  "text": "All the preparations examined separated into two components, the major one migrating a t -11.8 x cm./sec./V./cm. and the minor at -11.3 x 10-6 em./ sec./V./cm. Because of the small difference in the mobilities of these electrophoretic components it was impossible to separate them and study their composition. They seem not to correspond to the protein and nucleoprotein components of the virus preparation, for in one experiment the separated whole virus contained both electro- , 1963) , so tests were made to find whether CYMV is serologically related to them and to cowpea mosaic virus, which is also transmitted by beetles [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Table 3 shows the sources of the viruses and antisera used in the tests. ",
